column2: A Job Queue specifically written for Android to easily schedule jobs (tasks) that run in the background, improving UX and application stability.

column5: removed codecov until coverage report is fixed.

* Fix KeepAliveTest

This CL fixes the KeepAliveTest to better handle the delay between
finishing a job and consumer going idle. I've also changed when
we save when a consumer is done. This would not have any effect on
real time but important for test stability.

WIP experimental job scheduler API

not completely sure about whether each job should be forwarded to the scheduler

to the final model

New NetworkUtil API with WIFI support. More tests around WIFI requirement.
Ethernet is also considered as WIFI since it is usually meant to be used for unmetered/fast connection #62

WIP WIFI requirement for jobs.

This CL introduces a new API to specify WIFI requirement for jobs with an optional
timeout. JobQueue, Params and Jobs API are implemented & test. Still need to
change the NetworkUtil to receive the connection type and also adds tests for
JobManager and do the necessary bindings. #62

Allow require network with a timeout.

This CL introduces a new Params API where the network requirement can be
set to timeout. It is useful if you want to run some requiest or inform
the user if you cannot after a certain time.
This is also a preliminary step to introduce WIFI requirement since it
is useless without a timeout (there are many devices which will never see
WIFI

Do not reset delays on restart. Instead, rely on wall clock on app restart.
The previous behavior can be activated from JobManager configuration. #68

Add support for delaying a group #41

This CL extends RetryConstraint to enable delaying a group.
When a group is delayed, any job added afterwards into that
group will also be affected. Like other delays, these delays
are not persistent between application re-launches.
